Keep protonfixes on for launcher GAMEIDs + pre-launch EA reconcile + env scrub

Three GLF-OS behaviors bundled in this patch:

1. Keep umu-protonfixes enabled for the well-known launcher GAMEIDs
   Faugus installs (ea-app, battle-net, epic-games-launcher,
   ubisoft-connect, rockstar-games-launcher, wargaming). Faugus
   disables protonfixes for any GAMEID that is not "umu*" and not
   numeric -- this wipes out the global-stage fixes that launchers
   like EA App depend on.

2. Reconcile the EA App version layout before each launch by calling
   faugus.ea_fix.update_ea_path(). The reconcile was previously only
   run from monitor_process at install time; but EA App auto-updates
   itself between launches, so the rename/sweep/symlink pass has to
   run on every relaunch for ea-app GAMEIDs.

3. Scrub Linux/desktop-only env vars before spawning umu-run for
   launcher GAMEIDs whose internal env serializer caps at ~32 KB.
   On NixOS the desktop session env baseline is ~17 KB; combined
   with what umu-launcher and pressure-vessel inject (LD_LIBRARY_PATH,
   STEAM_COMPAT_*, WINEDLLOVERRIDES) we cross 32 KB and EA App fails
   game launches with eax::foundation::serializeEnvironmentImpl
   "Cannot serialize environment: the result is too long, NNNNN"
   and the InvalidEnvironmentData telemetry event. We drop only
   Linux-only chrome (GObject Introspection, GTK, KDE, system-wide
   XDG dirs, Qt theming, Nix profiles, doc paths) and keep all vars
   Wine/Proton/winegstreamer might use.

--- a/faugus/runner.py
+++ b/faugus/runner.py
@@ -161,7 +161,20 @@
                     set_env("PROTONPATH", f"{self.default_runner}")
 
         if os.environ.get("GAMEID") != "winetricks-gui":
-            if "umu" not in os.environ.get("GAMEID", "") and not (os.environ.get("GAMEID", "").isnumeric()):
+            # GLF-OS: keep protonfixes enabled for the well-known launcher
+            # GAMEIDs that Faugus itself can install (ea-app, battle-net,
+            # epic-games, ubisoft-connect, rockstar-games-launcher,
+            # wargaming). Without this, EA App's EABackgroundService loops
+            # in auto-repair because the global-stage protonfixes (corefonts
+            # registry, dotnet stubs, ...) are never applied.
+            _glf_launcher_gameids = {
+                "ea-app", "battle-net", "epic-games-launcher",
+                "ubisoft-connect", "rockstar-games-launcher", "wargaming",
+            }
+            _glf_gameid = os.environ.get("GAMEID", "")
+            if (_glf_gameid not in _glf_launcher_gameids
+                    and "umu" not in _glf_gameid
+                    and not _glf_gameid.isnumeric()):
                 set_env("PROTONFIXES_DISABLE", "1")
 
         protonpath = os.environ.get("PROTONPATH")
@@ -214,6 +227,21 @@
 
         set_env("UMU_USE_STEAM", "1")
 
+        # GLF-OS: reconcile EA App version layout before each launch.
+        # EA App auto-updates between launches; the reconcile (rename
+        # staging dirs, sweep orphan archives, symlink stale registry
+        # version refs to the current dir) keeps the on-disk layout in
+        # sync with what EA Desktop expects to find at the paths Wines
+        # registry hardcodes. Without it EABackgroundService loads from
+        # the previous version dir and EA falls into the auto-repair
+        # loop.
+        if os.environ.get("GAMEID") == "ea-app":
+            try:
+                from faugus.ea_fix import update_ea_path
+                update_ea_path(os.environ.get("WINEPREFIX", ""))
+            except Exception as e:
+                print(f"GLF-OS: pre-launch EA reconcile failed: {e}")
+
         self.lock_prefix()
         self.execute_final_command()
 
